It seems we already have microsoft.codeanalysis.csharp-2.0.0 and microsoft.codeanalysis.csharp-2.0.0 (last version of the packages is 2.2.0 /cc @daxian-dbw -Should we update? ) and the next works well:
```powershell
$Source = @"
using System;
public class BasicTest
{
public static void PrintStars(string s) 
{ 
    if (int.TryParse(s, out var i)) { Console.WriteLine(new string('*', i)); } 
    else { Console.WriteLine("Cloudy - no stars tonight!"); } 
} 
}
"@
Add-Type -TypeDefinition $Source

[BasicTest]::PrintStars("3")
```
